<p><abbr>STAB</abbr> stands for "Same-Type Attack Bonus". When a Pokémon uses a move with the same type as one of its own types, it gets a STAB bonus added to damage rolls. Otherwise, STAB is 0.</p>
<p>When STAB applies, it is equal to the Modifier of the move's Move Power. For example, if DEX is being used as the Move Power, then STAB is equal to the pokémon's DEX modifier.</p>
<p><strong>Addendum:</strong> STAB cannot be negative, even if a pokémon's move power modifier is negative. Treat STAB as 0 in these cases.</p>
